e tests to understand whether students can suit Information Management Department or what kind of Information Management Department related job is more applicable for our students</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				Graduate Project Instruction and experiences sharing from junior and senior students</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n				Higher education counseling events from the department</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n				Sept. &ndash; Oct.</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"4\">\r\n				1. Get acquainted with students, and help students who need financial aids apply for scholarships or part time jobs<br />\r\n				2. Counseling with students who fail more than two subjects and students who have failed half of credits in one semester previously<br />\r\n				3. Provide discussion opportunities between the students and the senior students for issues about courses&rsquo; contents, lecturing and course selection advices<br />\r\n				4. Talk with class cadres to understand students&rsquo; attendance or any other special cases.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n				Nov. &ndash; Dec.</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"4\">\r\n				1. Collect students&rsquo; opinions before the Guide-Teacher Meeting and discuss it during the meeting<br />\r\n				2. Report students&rsquo; list who need counseling back to the meeting<br />\r\n				3. Individual students counseling after midterm<br />\r\n				4. Senior students introduce optional courses in the second semester</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n				Jan.</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"4\">\r\n				1. Hold class meetings and class cadres election for the next semester before the final exam<br />\r\n				2. Keep tracking and counseling with students who have low academic performance</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n				Major focuses in the second semester</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n				1. Assist students who needs transferring department, applying dual majors or minors<br />\r\n				- Department transfer applying in the second semester<br />\r\n				- Dual majors applying in the second semester<br />\r\n				- Minors and other programs applying in the second semester<br />\r\n				- Applying date for transferring departments to FJU: registry before the end of May, 2010</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n				1. Encourage students attend career counseling events and job fairs held by school<br />\r\n				2. Further education and career counseling for senior students</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n				Feb. &ndash; Mar.</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"4\">\r\n				1. Assist students who need financial aids applying for scholarships or part time jobs<br />\r\n				2. Provide counseling with students who failed more than two subjects and students who have failed half of total credits in one semester once before<br />\r\n				3. Advise students about course selection<br />\r\n				4. Talk with class cadres to understand students&rsquo; absent situations or any special cases.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n				Apr. - May</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"4\">\r\n				1. Collect students&rsquo; opinions before the Guide-Teacher Meeting and discuss it during the meeting<br />\r\n				2. Report students&rsquo; list who need counseling back to the meeting<br />\r\n				3. Individual counseling students with grades or other issues after midterm</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n				Jun.</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"4\">\r\n				1. Hold class meeting and class cadres election for next semester before final exam<br />\r\n				2. Keep tracking and counseling with students who have low academic performance (suspension due date for graduating students: May; suspension due date for non-graduating students: June)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n');
